Sentencas: Sr2Fe1.5-xNixMo0.5O6-delta (x = 0, 0.05, 0.1, 0.2, 0.4) (SFNM) materials have been synthesized by a sol-gel combustion method and studied towards application as cathode materials for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs).
Titulo: Synthesis and characterization of B-site Ni-doped perovskites Sr2Fe1.5-xNixMo0.5O6-δ (x=0, 0.05, 0.1, 0.2, 0.4) as cathodes for SOFCs

Sentencas: The crystal structure, microstructure, thermal expansion, element valence, conductivity and electrochemical properties have been characterized as a function of Ni content.
Titulo: Synthesis and characterization of B-site Ni-doped perovskites Sr2Fe1.5-xNixMo0.5O6-δ (x=0, 0.05, 0.1, 0.2, 0.4) as cathodes for SOFCs

Sentencas: The symmetrical structure of the cubic lattice in perovskite oxides is confirmed.
Titulo: Synthesis and characterization of B-site Ni-doped perovskites Sr2Fe1.5-xNixMo0.5O6-δ (x=0, 0.05, 0.1, 0.2, 0.4) as cathodes for SOFCs

Sentencas: SFNM powders possess the 3D interconnected network microstructure composed of nanoparticles.
Titulo: Synthesis and characterization of B-site Ni-doped perovskites Sr2Fe1.5-xNixMo0.5O6-δ (x=0, 0.05, 0.1, 0.2, 0.4) as cathodes for SOFCs

Sentencas: An increasing Ni substitution results in the unit cell shrinkage and the increase of thermal expansion coefficient (TEC).
Titulo: Synthesis and characterization of B-site Ni-doped perovskites Sr2Fe1.5-xNixMo0.5O6-δ (x=0, 0.05, 0.1, 0.2, 0.4) as cathodes for SOFCs

Sentencas: Furthermore, X-ray photoelectron spectroscopy (XPS) analysis shows that Ni basically exhibits a low oxidation state (Ni2+).
Titulo: Synthesis and characterization of B-site Ni-doped perovskites Sr2Fe1.5-xNixMo0.5O6-δ (x=0, 0.05, 0.1, 0.2, 0.4) as cathodes for SOFCs

Sentencas: Doped Ni2+ affects the equilibrium between Fe3+/Mo5+ and Fe2+/Mo6+, which is directly related to the conductivity.
Titulo: Synthesis and characterization of B-site Ni-doped perovskites Sr2Fe1.5-xNixMo0.5O6-δ (x=0, 0.05, 0.1, 0.2, 0.4) as cathodes for SOFCs

Sentencas: The SFNM conductivity was apparently improved, reaching 60 S cm(-1) at 450 degrees C when x 0.1, which is more than twice that of the Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-delta (SFM) sample.
Titulo: Synthesis and characterization of B-site Ni-doped perovskites Sr2Fe1.5-xNixMo0.5O6-δ (x=0, 0.05, 0.1, 0.2, 0.4) as cathodes for SOFCs

Sentencas: In addition, Sr2Fe1.4Ni0.1Mo0.5O6-delta (SFN0.1M) cathodes showed excellent electrochemical performance and lowest interface polarization resistance (R-p).
Titulo: Synthesis and characterization of B-site Ni-doped perovskites Sr2Fe1.5-xNixMo0.5O6-δ (x=0, 0.05, 0.1, 0.2, 0.4) as cathodes for SOFCs

Sentencas: The Rp of the SFN0.1M cathode was approximately 50% of that of the SFM cathode.
Titulo: Synthesis and characterization of B-site Ni-doped perovskites Sr2Fe1.5-xNixMo0.5O6-δ (x=0, 0.05, 0.1, 0.2, 0.4) as cathodes for SOFCs

Sentencas: Moreover, the maximum power densities of a single cell based on the SFN0.1M cathode were 0.92, 1.27 W cm(-2) at 700, 750 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Synthesis and characterization of B-site Ni-doped perovskites Sr2Fe1.5-xNixMo0.5O6-δ (x=0, 0.05, 0.1, 0.2, 0.4) as cathodes for SOFCs

Sentencas: The SFNM material is a type of potential cathode for IT-SOFCs.
Titulo: Synthesis and characterization of B-site Ni-doped perovskites Sr2Fe1.5-xNixMo0.5O6-δ (x=0, 0.05, 0.1, 0.2, 0.4) as cathodes for SOFCs
